There are two problems with the code. First, you [should compare `String`s using `equals`, not `==`](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/513832/how-do-i-compare-strings-in-java). Otherwise it can return false even for identical `String`s.

Second, `nextLine` will read from the `Scanner` up until after the next newline. But `nextInt` only will read up until before that newline, so your first call to `nextLine` simply advances the `Scanner` by one character and returns an empty `String`. You need to call an extra `nextLine` after `nextInt` to advance onto the next line after your integer. For more information, see [this question](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13102045/scanner-is-skipping-nextline-after-using-next-or-nextfoo).

So you should make the following changes to your code:

    Scanner scanner = new Scanner(new File(&quot;submit.txt&quot;));

    int trials = scanner.nextInt();
